What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Fruit Concentrate Market?

Market Analysis and Size

Fruit concentrates are healthiest made from 100% fruit without additives such as added sugar or salt. For instance, a 4-ounce (120-ml) glass of orange juice which is prepared from concentrate delivers 280% vitamin C of the Daily Value (DV). This nutrient plays a significant role in immunity and wound healing. The fruit concentration is inexpensive and easy for transportation and storage because it helps increase the product's shelf-life. Increasing consciousness regarding health among consumers and growing demand for natural food products are the major factor boost the market growth.

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the fruit concentrate market was valued at USD 2152.60 million in 2022 and is expected to reach USD 6359.27 million by 2030, registering a CAGR of 14.50% during the forecast period of 2023 to 2030. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include in-depth expert analysis, geographically represented company-wise production and capacity, network layouts of distributors and partners, detailed and updated price trend analysis and deficit analysis of supply chain and demand.

